      "content": "hey, i think my smart thermostat is acting weird. whenever i get really stressed or frustrated, the temp drops like a few degrees almost instantly. i know it's supposed to be smart but it feels like it's responding to my mood specifically. is there some kind of sensor in there that picks up on more than just air temp?",
