      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just don't get why the \"coincidence\" is so consistent. like, what if they don't need cameras? i was reading about how smart devices use ultrasonic patterns or even just the way the electricity usage fluctuates in the lines to detect movement or presence in a room. if they can sense a person is there through vibrations or electrical signals, wouldn't that be enough to track my behavior? it feels like there's a way for them to gather data on me without it being obvious.",
